description.narrative: (Indonesia): The Bantu project will provide specialized, high-level technical assistance to USAID, USAID-funded programs, the Government of Indonesia (GOI) (e.g. Ministry of Health), parastatal organizations (e.g., Eijkman Institute), sub-national government (e.g., district health office), non-governmental organizations (NGOs), civil society organizations (CSOs), academic institutions, and other research institutes as required. Through the provision of targeted technical assistance, BANTU will support the USAID Maternal Child Health (MCH), TB and HIV teams to conduct special studies and support USAID-led workshops with GOI. .The targeted technical expertise that BANTU provides contributes to the U.S. Mission efforts to elevate Indonesia's global and regional role promoting democratic values, rule of law, and protecting the environment, public health, and other shared priorities. Indonesia's progress across the various health sector concerns supports its long-term economic prosperity. The role of BANTU directly contributes to U.S. Government and Indonesian efforts to improve public health outcomes in MNH, TB and pandemic disease, which is aligned with the Journey to Self-Reliance Framework. The activity supports the Mission objective of Indonesia models good governance practices (manifested in public services, public policy, and legal/regulatory framework) to promote the development of a healthy, educated, and skilled population to drive inclusive economic growth. Accordingly, Indonesia increases responsiveness to the public by demonstrating accountability and consistently providing essential services...
